<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="dawn-n">dawn <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /dɔːn/    美 /dɔːn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c-u">1.★ <strong>[C] &amp; [U] 黎明；拂晓：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>from dawn till dusk 
从早到晚</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The train left late that night and arrived in Montreal <strong>at dawn</strong> the next morning.  
火车深夜启程，第二天黎明时分到达了蒙特利尔。</p><footer>人教③ – 5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We arrived in Sydney as <strong>dawn broke</strong>. 
天亮时，我们抵达悉尼。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>开端；起始：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The book is about the <strong>dawn of civilization</strong>. 
这本书讲述文明的起源。</p></div></div>